        examples=[{"title": "Search in Rotated Array", "code": "def search_rotated(arr, target):\n    lo, hi = 0, len(arr) - 1\n    while lo <= hi:\n        mid = (lo + hi) // 2\n        if arr[mid] == target: return mid\n        if arr[lo] <= arr[mid]:  # left half sorted\n            if arr[lo] <= target < arr[mid]: hi = mid - 1\n            else: lo = mid + 1\n        else:                    # right half sorted\n            if arr[mid] < target <= arr[hi]: lo = mid + 1\n            else: hi = mid - 1\n    return -1\n\nprint(search_rotated([4,5,6,7,0,1,2], 0))  # 4", "output": "4", "explanation": "<p>Classic interview problem — one half of a rotated array is always sorted; use that to decide which half to explore.</p>"}],
